<span id="freeTextContainer1668137451263864640"><strong>Boring reading</strong><br/><br/>The book started ok, but it rambled on and repeated itself a lot.<br/>There wasn&apos;t much suspense or cleverly written chapters and it was a bit too easy to read with cheesy paragraph headings every few sentences.<br/>The author spent too long on areas of the story that weren&apos;t that interesting, for example the comments at her memorial service from people that knew Nancy went on for page after page and became boring because all the comments were so similar.<br/>I only got half way through and have </span>
  <span id="freeText1668137451263864640" style="display:none"><strong>Boring reading</strong><br /><br />The book started ok, but it rambled on and repeated itself a lot.<br />There wasn't much suspense or cleverly written chapters and it was a bit too easy to read with cheesy paragraph headings every few sentences.<br />The author spent too long on areas of the story that weren't that interesting, for example the comments at her memorial service from people that knew Nancy went on for page after page and became boring because all the comments were so similar.<br />I only got half way through and have up reading it because it wasn't challenging me or my imagination, mainly due to the over simplistic writing style. Sorry but not a favourite of mine.</span>
