<span id="freeTextContainer7589987626525175624"><strong>True Crime</strong><br/><br/>I don&apos;t know if growing up with a Law Enforcement Officer, my Father, started my interest in true crime, but it&apos;s been a life long interest. There are a lot of true crime books out there, but in my opinion, the best ones being the stories to life. Reading you get a sense of all the people involved, making the victims and survivors human. Amanda Lamb has certainly brought Nancy Cooper and her family and friends to life in this well written tale, bringing to light the sad but true fact t</span>
  <span id="freeText7589987626525175624" style="display:none"><strong>True Crime</strong><br /><br />I don't know if growing up with a Law Enforcement Officer, my Father, started my interest in true crime, but it's been a life long interest. There are a lot of true crime books out there, but in my opinion, the best ones being the stories to life. Reading you get a sense of all the people involved, making the victims and survivors human. Amanda Lamb has certainly brought Nancy Cooper and her family and friends to life in this well written tale, bringing to light the sad but true fact that domestic violence doesn't always show up in bruises and broken bones. </span>
