    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3304326966" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2110246602023868877">More like a 3.5. I enjoyed reading about Nancy and Brad’s story, albeit a very sad one, and grew to love Nancy’s family throughout. That being said, there is a lot of repetition that was unnecessary in my opinion - much of the story could’ve been significantly condensed, which would’ve made for a quicker read - and most of it was biased towards Nancy’s friends and family - the latter didn’t necessarily bother me but it would have been nice to hear more of Brad’s/his family’s side of the story an</span>
  <span id="freeText2110246602023868877" style="display:none">More like a 3.5. I enjoyed reading about Nancy and Brad’s story, albeit a very sad one, and grew to love Nancy’s family throughout. That being said, there is a lot of repetition that was unnecessary in my opinion - much of the story could’ve been significantly condensed, which would’ve made for a quicker read - and most of it was biased towards Nancy’s friends and family - the latter didn’t necessarily bother me but it would have been nice to hear more of Brad’s/his family’s side of the story and I can see how others may not appreciate the one-sided account. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2110246602023868877" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
